    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-04-12T00:05:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-04-12T00:05:00-05:00" n="686"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d686">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">357.AB/4–1252: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Pakistan</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d686fn1">This telegram was repeated to Karachi (priority)
                        and for information to London (priority) and New York.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-04-12T00:05:00-05:00"
                            >April 12, 1952—12:05 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1048. Re Kashmir.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>
                        <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> understands <gloss target="#t_GOP1"
                            >GOP</gloss> reply April 11, to <persName corresp="#p_GDF1"
                            >Graham</persName> re his proposals not favorable. End <gloss
                            target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>On assumption <persName corresp="#p_KCSM1">Zafrulla</persName>’s remarks
                        to you, when you presented our views in <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                            >Deptel</gloss> 1029 of April 9, were in similar vein, we request you,
                        if you deem timing and situation appropriate, indicate our concern over
                            <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> position.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>We suggest your comments might be following: <list>
                            <label>A.</label>
                            <item>We know of no more constructive step which can be taken at this
                                time.</item>
                            <label>B.</label>
                            <item>We believe continuance <persName corresp="#p_GDF1"
                                    >Graham</persName>’s negots not inimical to <gloss
                                    target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> interests.</item>
                            <label>C.</label>
                            <item>Acceptance proposals wld enable <gloss target="#t_GOP1"
                                    >GOP</gloss> maintain strong position established as result past
                                record firm coop with <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>.</item>
                            <label>D.</label>
                            <item>Failure <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName> negots due
                                parties’ nonacceptance proposals might well jeopardize two <gloss
                                    target="#t_UNCIP1">UNCIP</gloss> res.</item>
                            <label>E.</label>
                            <item>Bringing <gloss target="#t_PlebAd1">PlebAd</gloss> into negots now
                                wld constitute step forward.</item>
                            <label>F.</label>
                            <item>In view <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss>’s known desire for
                                peaceful settlement, we hope <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss>
                                will appreciate advantages of accepting <persName corresp="#p_GDF1"
                                    >Graham</persName>’s proposals.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>You are requested consult with <gloss target="#t_UKHC1">UKHC</gloss> prior
                        making this approach. London please keep in touch with <gloss
                            target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
